For those interested in following the progress of the flag desecration amendment through Congress, go to:<br>
          <br>
http://thomas.loc.gov/home/c105query.html<br><br>
and search on bill number:<br><br>
h.j.res. 54<br><br>
The amendment has something like 270 sponsors.  It is worded as follows:<br><br>
&quot;The Congress shall have the power to prohibit physical desecration of the flag of the United States.&quot;<br><br>
Please note that this amendment will NOT over-rule previous Supreme Court decisions that specified that acts of flag desecration are constitutionally-protected free speech.  In order to do that, the bill would have to say something like:<br><br>
&quot;Acts of physical desecration of the flag of the United States are not speech acts and are not protected by the First Amendment to this Constitution.&quot;<br><br>
If this amendment is adopted and ratified as currently worded, any bill that Congress passes (e.g.,See H.R. 1556) to prohibit flag desecration will still have to respect the First Amendment's prohibition of laws that restrict free speech.  Since the Supreme Court has previously (and repeatedly) ruled that flag desecration is constitutionally protected free speech, the new amendment will have no teeth. <br>
It will be like a zit on the face of the Constitution, i.e., a cosmetic defect that does not affect its function.<br><br>
The Congressional prostitutes who are supporting this bill are for the most part lawyers and know this all too well.  This bill has nothing to do with legislation and everything to do with jingoist posturing, and use of the flag as a cover for the ignorance, bigotry, intolerance, and infinite corruptibility of most of its supporters.   <br><br>
I doubt that any amendment that specifically redefines free speech or in any way explicitily restricts the applicability of the First Amendment would get the support that this phoney &quot;amendment&quot; has received.  What this flag desecration amendment really does is provide fuel for the future reelection campaign propaganda blurbs of the fanatics who support it.  Their eagerness to use the Constitution for such purposes only further demonstrates how morally and intellectually corrupt they have all become.<br><br>
John M. Stassi<br>
